Scores of ANC supporter and ordinary citizens came together in their numbers to bid farewell to the “mother of the nation“. The funeral venue in Orlando Stadium is surrounded by police in almost all the entrances. The Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) supporters also came in numbers and were seen singing along with ANC supporters in honour of Madikizela Mandela. EFF leader Julius Malema is expected to be among those who will be speaking at the funeral on Saturday. At the same time, metro police department urged residents and mourners to use public transport to go to the stadium as it’s the only mode of transport will be allowed in the area. The funeral procession has now arrived in Orlando Stadium. The funeral was scheduled to start at 8:00 am on Saturday. Mama will be laid to her final resting place in Fourways North of Johannesburg. -TNA Reporter